===Other===
* Cogman also wrote the hour-long series of animated featurettes included in the TV season Blu ray set for Season 1 (narrated by the TV series' starring cast, in-character), known as the &quot;[[Complete Guide to Westeros]]&quot;. Although [[Dave Hill]] took over the writing responsibilities for the new format known as the &quot;[[Histories &amp; Lore]]&quot; series, Cogman still oversaw it.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[http://winteriscoming.net/2012/02/22/inside-the-creation-of-the-game-of-thrones-box-set-with-bryan-cogman/]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
* HBO Making Game of Thrones blog for Season 1.
* Author of the 2012-released series guide book [[Inside HBO's Game of Thronesâ&euro;&#x17D;â&euro;&#x17D;]].
* The sigil next to Cogman's name in the opening credits is actually a vomiting maester - a joke by Benioff and Weiss, referencing how at a certain season wrap party, Cogman had too much to drink and had to throw up.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.denofgeek.us/tv/game-of-thrones/243771/67-things-you-didnt-know-about-game-of-thrones-season-4 ]&lt;/ref&gt;

